hw7:
based off example 15
Using normal maps to add new details to textures

Use T to cycle through the textures, then N to cycle through the normal maps for that texture. 
Also, make sure to hit M so that the normals are actually being calculated

I took the NoWally textures from last week and used them as textures here. 
Then I used the matching Wally textures to build normal maps. 
Some of them I only gave defined normals to Wally, others the whole image.
Some of them I actually converted into normal maps (correctly colored with normals), others I just left the colors as is.

Used to find where wally was in images he was removed from
4 normal modes
plain: normal colored wally on a blue background
just: plain converted to a normal map
whole: whole origional image converted to normal map
junk/origional: the origional image, junk data that doesn't make sence as a normal

plain and junk/origional both have their normals oriented incorrectly, so when used to calculate lighting it's nonsense. 
just highlights the ghost of wally in the image
Whole highlights ALL the edges in the origional image, including where wally is, which is still highlighted on the texture without wally

CSCI4239/5239 Spring 2026



Key bindings
  m          Toggle shaders
  o          Change objects
  t			 Change textures
  n			 Change normal map
  s          Toggle light movement
  <>+-       Move light
  arrows     Change view angle
  PgDn/PgUp  Zoom in and out
  0          Reset view angle
  ESC        Exit


